1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,840
早安,兄弟姊妹,父母,祖父母,孩子,年輕人,所有人!

2
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:14,300
兄弟姊妹,朋友,祖父母,父母,所有小朋友,早安!

3
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:16,840
早安!

4
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:23,900
哇,真是太高興了,我們可以讓所有人一起在這裏敬拜神!

5
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:29,700
我們實在很高興,我們今天可以一起來到這裏,敬拜神!

6
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:34,600
I remember last time when I was here, it was the Thanksgiving day.

7
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:39,000
我記得上次來的時候,就是上年的感恩節。

8
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:46,400
I was so touching to see family members worship together as one big group.

9
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:52,400
我們見到不同的家庭,就是同一個 unit 一齊去敬拜神,實在令我好感動。

10
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:55,600
Today I witnessed that again here today.

11
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,400
今天我又再次見到了。

12
00:00:57,400 --> 00:01:02,300
Last time especially, I was so touched that when I see everyone,

13
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:07,400
the adults are laying hands on the children and youth to say a blessing on them.

14
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:10,600
上次你記不記得,我們見到有祖父母,有父母,

15
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:14,500
把祂的手按在我們的小朋友上面去祝福他們。

16
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:19,000
But it is regardless of if they are blood related.

17
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:25,200
Some adults, they don't have children around, or youth, they don't have any parents around them.

18
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:30,600
They still get the blessing from someone in this big family to lay hands on them.

19
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:34,100
但是這個祝福的關係不止於一個血緣關係,

20
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:37,900
因為我們知道有一些弟兄姊妹說他們沒有小朋友,

21
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:42,500
但是他們仍然用他們的手按在下一代,去祝福他們。

22
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:47,500
That is to show God's love among us like one big family.

23
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:49,100
Let's say praise the Lord together.

24
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:53,500
就是這樣見到我們神的祝福在我們中間,我們一起說讚美主。

25
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:55,700
Praise the Lord.

26
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:58,500
Very good. And today we are going to do that again.

27
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:02,100
我們今天也會再次一起去這樣做。

28
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:05,400
You see that this is not a 禮事。

29
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:08,200
所以你看到這個不是一個紅包,不是一個禮事。

30
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,000
But you know, I am a children pastor.

31
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,100
I've got all the props and everything here.

32
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:18,700
但是我是一個傳道人,所以我一向都有齊這些法寶在裡面。

33
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:21,500
Yeah, that is 法寶, you know.

34
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:24,500
Traditious stuff.

35
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:26,700
有很多不同的種類的東西。

36
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:31,500
So before we worship God together, let's bow down to have a word of prayer.

37
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:34,100
讓我們一起祈禱。

38
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:36,800
Dear Father God, you are worthy to be praised.

39
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:39,100
稱為天父,我們讚美你。

40
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:43,000
Thank you for giving us a church, that community,

41
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,000
so that we can learn to love and support one another.

42
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,300
多謝你給到我們這個教會的群體,

43
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:51,300
讓我們學習去愛,去愛你,去愛人。

44
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:55,500
And we could worship together like a big, big family in Christ.

45
00:02:55,500 --> 00:03:00,100
實在很感恩,在基督裡我們就是一個大家庭一起去敬拜你。

46
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:05,000
As we open the Bible, please let us learn more of your teaching.

47
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:10,000
當我們打開你自己給我們的話語,聖經的時候,讓我們學習。

48
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,200
And follow you more closely.

49
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:15,200
我們亦都可以緊緊地去跟隨你。

50
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:18,400
We ask for your presence to be with us this morning.

51
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:22,400
我求你將你的祝福臨下到我們每一個人身上。

52
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,800
Let us worship you with a humble heart.

53
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,400
讓我們用一個謙卑的心去敬拜你。

54
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:31,700
May you open our heart, our eyes, our ears to receive your precious word.

55
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:36,200
讓你開我們的心,開我們的眼,開我們的耳朵,

56
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:38,200
去接受你自己給我們的話語。

57
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:40,000
We pray in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.

58
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,700
奉主耶穌基督,聖名以祈求。

59
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:45,700
We say together, Amen.

60
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:50,200
When was the last time that you received a personal letter?

61
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:55,200
你記不記得上一次你什麼時候收到一份真的給你的一封信呢?

62
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:59,800
These days, we use a lot of email, WhatsApp, WeChat, and all that.

63
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:04,800
We almost forget the feeling to have a letter, a real letter in our hand.

64
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:09,200
因為你知道我們很用短信、email,各樣種類,

65
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:13,000
很久都沒有收到一封有信封寄給你的信了。

66
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:18,500
I remember the first letter that I got in my hand when I was young.

67
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:21,500
我記得我小時候,我真的收到一封信,

68
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:23,500
當我第一封信收到的時候,

69
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:24,500
I was so happy.

70
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:26,000
我真的很開心。

71
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:31,000
So that's why after I became a children pastor at my church, R3C,

72
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:37,000
當我在成北華基做兒童傳道人的時候,

73
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:41,000
even though we have around 900 children on our list,

74
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:44,500
我大概有900個小朋友在我們的list。

75
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:50,500
But I decided every month I'm going to write down a birthday card

76
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:54,000
for each one of the students that was having birthday that month.

77
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,000
我當時下定決心,

78
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:01,000
我就要親自寫一封生日卡給每一個小朋友的。

79
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:07,000
So that's the birthday card for that birthday boy or girl of the month.

80
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:12,000
I wrote a note, a handwritten note for them.

81
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,500
這個就是其中一張的卡。

82
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:18,000
在每一張卡裡面,我真的親手寫上祝福他的說話。

83
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:21,500
And I put on beautiful stickers on each one of them.

84
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:24,000
當然,小朋友喜歡貼紙的,

85
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,000
我都把貼紙放在裡面。

86
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
And then I put it in the envelope.

87
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,000
然後我就放在信封裡面了。

88
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:35,000
It was good, I have a helper that helped me at least to print the address.

89
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:39,500
當然,我又同工幫手把一些地址放上去。

90
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:43,000
We put the stamp on it and put it in the postage mail.

91
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,000
然後就寄了。

92
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Well, you may ask, why board? Why didn't I give it to them on Sunday?

93
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:56,000
或者你會問我,為什麼你不簡單,禮拜天就直接給他們呢?

94
00:05:56,000 --> 00:06:01,000
So at least it will save the effort and the money for putting it in the postage mail.

95
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,000
那你又可以省一筆,不用放郵票嗎?

96
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:07,000
But then, the parents are telling me.

97
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,000
但這些父母他會這樣跟我說。

98
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Every time when the kids are receiving the letter in the postage mail, they were so happy.

99
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:22,000
每一次他們真的在郵箱裡拿到一封給他們的信,他們真的超開心。

100
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:27,000
They open it and they read each of the notes that I have handwritten on them.

101
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:32,000
他們就開來看,然後慢慢逐粒字這樣去讀出來。

102
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:36,000
It shows them that the children pastor love them.

103
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:42,000
讓他們知道,他們的兒童傳道人是很愛他們的。

104
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,000
And also God loves them too.

105
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,000
還有神是很愛他們的。

106
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,000
So, how about you?

107
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
或者你又怎樣呢?

108
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Do you know that every day we are also receiving a letter?

109
00:06:56,000 --> 00:07:00,000
其實你知不知道我們每一天都收到一封信?

110
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,000
What's that?

111
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,000
That is a letter from God because it is in the Bible.

112
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:10,000
這個就是神給我們的一封信,就是祂的聖經。

113
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:14,000
This is God's letter to us every day, every moment.

114
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:20,000
這個聖經就是神給我們的一封信,給我們每一天的一封信,每一刻的一封信。

115
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Just then we have seen the skit, it is saying that when God is praising us in the Bible,

116
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:30,000
He always say, "Oh, it is for me."

117
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:35,000
這個短劇都知道了,當我們看的時候,其實對我們說的說話。

118
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:42,000
That is for me, but when the Bible is rebuking us and say, "It is for Pastor Ada."

119
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:46,000
當我們見到一些好的說話,就當然是跟我說了,天父。

120
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:50,000
但當我們見到一些好像責備人的說話,就當然是跟旁邊的人說了。

121
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,000
For her, not for me.

122
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,000
就是給她的,不是我的。

123
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:58,000
But in fact, God is the whole Bible, every word is for each one of us.

124
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:06,000
但如果我們深信聖經是神給我們一封完全的信的時候,其實每一個字都是對我們每一個人說話。

125
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:10,000
Let me going to tell you a story.

126
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
我現在很想跟你們分享一個故事。

127
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:17,000
That story is called "Sydney and Norman".

128
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:22,000
這個故事就叫做"Sydney and Norman".

129
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Because one day, they are also receiving a letter from God.

130
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:32,000
因為這兩個朋友有一天收到神給他們的一封信。

131
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:39,000
You see, the one that is on the left, that you can see, that is Sydney.

132
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:43,000
在左邊那位朋友就叫做Sydney。

133
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:47,000
And the one on the right, that little pig, is called Norman.

134
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:50,000
右邊那位豬朋友就叫做Norman。

135
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:54,000
豬朋友,不是豬朋友,是狗友。

136
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,000
So I am going to tell you the story from here.

137
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
我很想跟你分享這個故事。

138
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:04,000
Once, there were two pigs living on the same street.

139
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:09,000
從前,在這條街裡面住了兩隻豬。

140
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:13,000
They lived next to each other, but they don't know each other's name.

141
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:16,000
他們是鄰居,但是他們不知道彼此的名字。

142
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,000
Why?

143
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,000
為什麼呢?

144
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:25,000
Because the one that is on the right, Norman, always get up early for work.

145
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:30,000
因為右邊那位Norman,他經常都很早起床就去上班。

146
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:34,000
But you see, the one on the left, even always have the ketchup mark on the tie,

147
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:37,000
that is Sydney, always getting up late.

148
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:40,000
但是左邊那位Sydney,就經常都很晚起床的,

149
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,000
就把衣服弄得很髒。

150
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Norman is a very good pig.

151
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,000
Norman實在是很豬。

152
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Niche and tidy.

153
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,000
很整齊,很清潔。

154
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:55,000
He always follow all the different rules when he was young at school.

155
00:09:55,000 --> 00:10:00,000
他小時候在學校的時候,就會守秩序。

156
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,000
Get all the awards from school.

157
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,000
在學校是很用功的。

158
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,000
And when he grew up,當他長大的時候,

159
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:12,000
The boss always pat on his shoulder and say, "Good job, Norman."

160
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:17,000
他的老闆都跟他說, "好,做得好呀,做得好呀,Norman."

161
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:19,000
And that's why he thought that,

162
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:23,000
God must be also very pleased of me, because I am such a good pig.

163
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Norman就覺得,神應該對我都十分驕傲,

164
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,000
我這麼好的豬,對不對?

165
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:32,000
And then he look down on all the other pigs.

166
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,000
They are not doing well.

167
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,000
其他那些小豬,真的沒有我這麼好的。

168
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:40,000
Wondering why it is so hard for them to be good.

169
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,000
其實也不是有多難,做好豬,對不對?

170
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,000
不是。

171
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,000
Yes, that's it.

172
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,000
And then there is Sidney.

173
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,000
有這隻豬,Sidney了。

174
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,000
He is such a messy pig.

175
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,000
Sidney真是鬧那麼久。

176
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:58,000
He always cannot follow any rules, whether it is at school or at work.

177
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:04,000
或者他在學校,在上班,他都不可以順從,守秩序的。

178
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,000
Always late.

179
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,000
經常都遲到的。

180
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:10,000
In school, always get sent to the principal office.

181
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:15,000
在學校,又經常都要被老師send到校長室。

182
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,000
And his boss always complain about him as well.

183
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:21,000
他的老闆又經常投訴他。

184
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:25,000
And that's why he thought, oh, I was such a messy and bad pig.

185
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:30,000
Sidney就說,我真是鬧那麼久,我真是一隻頑皮的豬。

186
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:33,000
God must be very frustrated with me and rejected me.

187
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:37,000
神當然對我很失望,祂當然不要我了。

188
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:40,000
He was very sad and thought that he was a total failure.

189
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:44,000
其實他自己都很傷心,他覺得自己是一個失敗。

190
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:49,000
One day, both of them received a mail in the mailbox.

191
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:53,000
有一日,兩隻豬仔都同樣在信箱收到一封信。

192
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,000
What is it?

193
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,000
是什麼來的呢?

194
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:58,000
It was an invitation from God.

195
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:01,000
原來是神發出一個邀請信。

196
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:06,000
He invited both of them to go to his house at 77 M Street.

197
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:13,000
原來神邀請他們來到神的自己的家,77號M Street。

198
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:18,000
Yes, want to talk to each one of them individually.

199
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:23,000
因為神想對著他們,親自跟他們說些話。

200
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:28,000
Oh, Sidney was panicking.

201
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,000
Sidney簡直是手抖腳抖。

202
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,000
You have to do this.

203
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:36,000
He was so panic.

204
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,000
真的很緊張,很害怕。

205
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:43,000
